Instructions

1. Register your app in https://console.firebase.google.com/
2. Create config.js and config.php in src folder by config.example.js and config.example.php with your firebase configs
3. Install any web server (for example, ngrok)
4. Run npm install
5. Run docker-compose up --build -d
6. Run npm run dev
7. Run ngrok http 80
8. Open url from ngrok in browser
9. Run docker-compose exec php bash
10. Run php src/index.php

Now you send messages to your app via firebase)
You can see messages in your app in browser console and notifications(if it was a background message) or in browser window(if it was a foreground message)
